{"id": "3267", "post": "<div class=\"post-3267 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-kansas-city tag-virpus-com tag-xen\" id=\"post-3267\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/virpus-30year-512mb-xen-vps-in-kansas-city/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Virpus \u2013 $30/Year 512MB Xen VPS in Kansas City</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/kansas-city/\" rel=\"tag\">kansas city</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/virpus-com/\" rel=\"tag\">virpus.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/xen/\" rel=\"tag\">xen</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> December 24, 2012 @ 11:52 pm, by Zahra</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"http://virpus.com/\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/virpus.jpg.webp\" class=\"screenshot litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/virpus.jpg.webp\" alt=\"Virpus\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a><em>Kenneth</em>, from <a href=\"http://virpus.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Virpus</a>, has emailed us a few Xen PV offers that they\u2019re offering on yearly terms.</p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>512MB Xen Plan</strong><p></p><ul><li>2 CPU Core</li><li>512MB RAM</li><li>1024MB SWAP</li><li>20GB Disk Space Raid 10</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>3 IPv6 Address</li><li>Xen/SolusVM</li><li>1000GB Bandwidth</li><li>100Mbps Port Speed</li><li>$30/Year \u2013&nbsp;<a href=\"https://myvirpus.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=151\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></li><li>Location: Kansas City</li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>1024 MB Xen Plan</strong><p></p><ul><li>4 CPU Core</li><li>1024MB RAM</li><li>2048MB SWAP</li><li>40GB Disk Space Raid 10</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>3 IPv6 Address</li><li>Xen/SolusVM</li><li>2000GB Bandwidth</li><li>100Mbps Port Speed</li><li>$60/Year &nbsp;\u2013&nbsp;<a href=\"https://myvirpus.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=152\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></li><li>Location: Kansas City</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Virpus have been featured <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/?s=virpus.com&amp;searchsubmit=Find\" target=\"_blank\">regularly</a> on LowEndBox since January 2010. Their last offer on here was posted back in September when they were advertising a <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/virpus-4-50-512mb-xen-vps-in-kansas-city/\">$4.50 512MB Xen VPS in Kansas City</a>. Reviews were mixed \u2013 so I suggest you take a look and have a read for yourself. Nodes are utilizing the&nbsp;E5-2620 CPU, hardware RAID 10 and have 64GB of RAM. The offer will end on the 31st December (New Years Eve).<br>\n<span id=\"more-3267\"></span><br>\nVirpus offer a 99.9% uptime guarantee and provision virtual servers once the customer has passed any fraud tests. Unlike their last offer, this time around they\u2019re not including DirectAdmin for free but they will license it at a monthly rate of $7/mo, and will license cPanel at $12/mo. You would need to open a support ticket at their helpdesk to get this setup (by default, their order form would bill you yearly). Further information can be ascertained by reading their <a href=\"http://virpus.com/legal/terms.html\">Terms of Service</a> and their <a href=\"http://virpus.com/legal/privacy.html\">Privacy Policy</a>.</p><p><strong>Network Information:</strong></p><p>Servers are located in Kansas City, Missouri. More information regarding their network and infrastructure can be found <a href=\"http://virpus.com/infrastructure\">here</a>.</p><p>Test IPv4: 199.180.132.43<br>\nTest File:&nbsp;<a href=\"htt